The need for speed The Run is fighting across America.
Revision
Originally a hassle-free race turns into a set of stupid mistakes by people who have nothing to do with a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills to some extent the ambition of everyone but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the older Need for Speed racing series and to come out a kind of game from playable games that would not count only with points.
So we were curious how the added passages are going to be during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible faineantism on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are taken on the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race is done on a different route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also quite nice even if the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
In addition, the tests are occasionally embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you need to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Apart from this, the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a small number of them, but that is enough.
There are moments you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then again you expect another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who get into the game and try to make you the difficult situation.
The novelty is the passages outside the vehicle.
It’s more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping on the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than what you expect (to be specific, there are only three).
The result is just like that because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that embellish the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at the moment there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said that it is negative.
As for the realistic simulation, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of racing design.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
In contrast to the driving model, collisions are not yet fully developed.
We don’t expect this game to be a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don’t have, in a collision with any object, any idea of how your car behaves, it’s not completely good.
During the tight overtakings you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy volts.
Or it ends up in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken the figure or you are out in the scenery the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you must start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes reboots don't help and you have to find the solution by remembering the route piece in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions end up in the same places.
For example, there are certain curves that you have to go through in a certain way otherwise it does not happen.
Otherwise, you will encounter "civil" vehicles in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either put yourself aside and bypass them or brake.
It does not matter if you go in front of him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always comes very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
During all the time of the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This is most annoying at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a number of times.
We can understand that the goal of this game is to do something exciting and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it is a pity because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you do not have time to follow everything that happens.
And it does not matter if it is because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance to get bored or anything else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You should pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic rides on very technical drives for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a metro train that sends the car directly to the scrapyard.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What's bothering is that in more extreme situations, the imagery doesn't hold up and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true for accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful for you.
The sound part is good and the track is the choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack was created in the style of "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it is the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for mistakes to hit your eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The students of velvet in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from the high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts organized on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the Rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes concert that takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of velvet" is held in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University take place.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate International Student Day with dignity and commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public the highest level of choral music and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Smells in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, medical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Those interested will find all the information on the festival’s website www.festaacademica.cz.
