If someone were to search for the word that expresses IBM’s strategy as closely as possible, the closest would be “the long-term.”
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a company felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first head, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
Its slogan "Think!" became the imprint around which the life of a giant future will grow (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of the company culture carefully developed by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thinking of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This allowed us during our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more" delayed for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to take care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM's people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed reward system for inventors and merchants.
In the same way, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was at the beginning brilliant in discovering talents- as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman – Virginia Rometty – who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for thirty years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
