Colom endorses Portillo's extradition to the United States
President <0xC3><0x81>lvaro Colom announced last Tuesday that he had ordered the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo to answer to the United States for the conspiracy to launder $70 million.
Thus ends the trial for Guatemala to respond to the request of the northern country that called for Portillo to be tried there.
In a press conference, Colom stated that his decision obeys the independence of the judiciary and executive branch, taking into account the fact that a court of first instance had already ordered his extradition.
He claimed that during his tenure "he did not help" in any judicial resolution and he had given way to all the extraditions he had known.
