What Colom has done involves an executive approach after exhausting all the judicial and constitutional proceedings to judge the former proxy for the 2004-2004 interval.
According to the resolutions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Constitutional Court (CC), Portillo should be extradited after resolving his legal situation in Guatemala and guaranteeing his human rights.
Portillo was absolved for embezzlement of $120 million from the Department of Defense when he was president, which was the pre-extradition trial, but the Department of Public Prosecutions appealed and reactivated the case.
Trinijove helped 6,000 young people at risk
The entity was born to avoid the marginalization of young people without training
The record of the first 25 years of life of the social support entity Trinijove is important: 6,000 young people at risk of exclusion have received help to overcome a difficult situation during this quarter century.
This is in addition to the long centenary of jobs currently obtained by this social group.
The anniversary served yesterday to take stock in an event celebrated in a former industrial complex of Fabra i Coats that more than 300 people attended.
Trinijove was born in the neighbourhood of Trinitat Vella in 1986 with the aim of helping people who are poorly educated, unemployed, with drug problems or marginalized.
Yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu concentrated a large number of officials of entities and institutions who in these 25 years have collaborated with the association.
The varied political representation, in the middle of the election season, showed the unitary nature of the work carried out by Trinijove.
Alongside the President of the Catalan Regional Government (Generalitat), Artur Mas and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, the event was attended by the former Minister of Socialist Education, Ernest Maragall and the former Deputy Mayor to the Mayor and current eco-socialist municipal councilor Ricard Goma.
The current Minister of Social Welfare and Family, Josep Llu<0xC3><0xAD>s Cleries, and the General Director of Charity of La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa, also attended in the large hall of Fabra i Coats.
Mas claimed that Trinijove was born in a very difficult time and the current one is too, but he added that the work done so far "is a good basis".
The president gave Trinijove as an example to know how to fight against bad circumstances and to give hope to people in difficulty.
“The crisis is not something new for the entity and for the work it does,” he said.
Property invaded by squatters for micro-festivals, evacuated
The invaders had appropriated 11 of the 13 apartments in the building, in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the property at noon yesterday without any resistance.
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare that the residents of 51 Balmes Street lived ended.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building they illegally occupied at noon yesterday and where they organized micro-festivals that desperate neighbors, in judicial order and without the need for a police intervention.
At the end of the operation, the door lock was changed to prevent the situation from happening again.
"From this day on, there will be access control," the administrator said.
The squatters, who had invaded 11 of the building's 13 apartments - the rest were inhabited - took away the electrical installation and some of the water, except to paint the walls and leave residue of all kinds, especially alcoholic beverage cans.
The first three apartments were the scene of the feasts of the masses, which lasted up to two days and despaired the tenants.
Next to the building there is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which was also affected.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, told Europa Press that as soon as the building was occupied his business fell by 80%.
The owner of the discotheque mentioned that the invaders of the property were unfair to her, because they sold the glasses for three euros, while in the discotheque they were worth 10.
In addition, the owner of the recreation room had to respond to the neighbors' complaints about the noise, while, according to her, the trouble was not caused by the customers of the discotheque, but by the inhabitants of the occupied house and especially the participants in the parties organized there, which were more frequent and intense in the last few weeks.
The head of the discotheque explained that the trouble was so great that she even reached an agreement with the owner of the building and it has been nine months that he "forgives" the rent.
The Guardia Urbana (municipal police) also confirmed that in recent weeks they had received more complaints from neighbors for this situation.
The president of the municipal group of the PP of the town hall, Alberto Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez D<0xC3><0xAD>az, had last week called for "the immediate evacuation of the building to end the problems of life in common and civility that it caused residents and the degradation of the area".
The popular leader explained that before the summer only one floor of the building was occupied, but in recent months squatters had occupied all the floors of the building and almost all the apartments and that in some apartments there were flights as well.
It is in this sense that he added that "it is necessary to end impunity and be ruthless against the antisocial behavior generated in property".
Also yesterday, the Mossos (the local Catalan police) evacuated a building in Nou Barris.
At 3.30 p.m., police moved to 35 Rue Mont-ral, after receiving a call from a neighbor who had observed four people accessing the building.
All four were arrested immediately.
Park or mountain?
The architects coincide on the opportunity of the convocation beyond the controversy on the fees
The municipal competition on the 16 doors reopens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the already extinct Metropolitan Corporation of Barcelona (CMB), this Administration printed posters promoting Collserola.
The brochure defined the mountain as the great park of metropolitan Barcelona.
In addition, it also contained a comparison, in figures, with New York’s Central Park.
With the death of the CMB in 1987, the park became again, in the imagination of many people, the upper limit of Barcelona, the Catalan capital being the only one that does not orient itself on the north-south axis, if not high (mountain) - low (sea).
The qualification of Collserola as a natural park is to the advantage of this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
This was the situation until, in September, the town hall convened a mega-competition composed of 16 contests for all the doors of access to Collserola.
A door brings back the idea of a park, no doubt.
That's it, or someone wants to put doors in the field.
The question arises: Collserola: park or mountain?
The competition, both in terms of its organization and in terms of reflection on the city, is a topic of conversation for all architects in Barcelona.
It's almost a recurring theme that two members of this ancient cast of elect speak when they recognize each other in an elevator.
And this is precisely one of the few opinions on which three architects from Barcelona, university professors, have presented themselves.
Miguel Rold<0xC3><0xA1>n, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the competition is timely.
For Rold<0xC3><0xA1>n, after approaching the coastal front "it is necessary" to debate on the "mountain front" because the speech of Ildefons Cerda, that of the green house p<0xC3><0xA2>tés was not carried out at the end.
“We have to start from the base that the most extensive park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things for its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex", the architect gave the verdict for which the title of "gates of Collserola" contains a "lexical trap": one should not think of these "as accesses to a park, but the delimitation of certain areas in which it is necessary to act".
Modol, like Rold<0xC3><0xA1>n and Bayona with experience in the urban world, calls the proposal an "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers".
Dangers that derive from "the uncertainty of the projection of public space" after the experience lived in the 80s and that had in the area of the Forum "his swan song".
The first fear is the very delimitation of the borders on which one can build.
“Limiting something means already establishing the next step,” that is, overcoming it.
“We need to think about new urban planning instruments, because the current ones [referring to the Metropolitan General Plan (MGP)] can cause real disasters.”
Speaking more on the issue, Modol believes that, by simplifying the El Valles de Collserola area "can be heard as a park, that of Barcelona, no".
Modol recalls that there is already a work done by the Board of Directors of Collserola that "must not be lost", thanking for the opportunity that the town hall offers to its corporation to intervene in this project "from the first moment".
In addition, he understands that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the safe-conduct that allows architects to enter the debate, but "doubts" whether this technical profile should lead the multidisciplinary teams ("any success", he says) that we have had to create: "We architects, should be only an instrument".
Bayona insinuates that the answer to the question that gives the title of this piece is complex, because of the basis of the competition there is a lack of a global vision of Collserola: "We have convened 16 cross-sectional competitions - he says - in the mountain-sea sense, but there is no longitudinal reading that sees and understands the area as a whole".
This means, at least in this case, that he has chosen to participate in the 16 contests.
In another way, a project so that one of the doors can collide in the program and definition with that of the neighboring door architect.
In his opinion, yes, the town hall should ensure that the band immediately superior to that of Ronda de Dalt should provide, in its entirety, an area of equipment that makes a smooth transition between the city and the green.
Casino forgives Jon<0xC3><0xA1>s Larraz<0xC3><0xA1>bal and he will be released
After 72 days of provisional arrest, Casino Red’s legal power attorney granted the mayor’s brother’s pardon for the trial initiated against him for alleged blackmail.
