This Monday, the founder of the legal power of the Casino Red, V<0xC3><0xAD>ctor Aldo Garc<0xC3><0xAD>a G<0xC3><0xB3>mez, appeared before the judge José Luis Pecina to seek forgiveness for the brother of the mayor of the region; therefore, he could recover his freedom in the following hours.
During the legal proceedings, the Public Prosecutor's Officer attached to the Tribunal, Ramiro Arias, questioned Garc<0xC3><0xAD>a G<0xC3><0xB3>mez whether the damage had been recovered and who associates of the gambling house had been the one who had granted the pardon, but the lawyer tried not to disclose the name.
In accordance with file 197/2011, Jon<0xC3><0xA1>s Larraz<0xC3><0xA1>bal is granted legal pardon and subsequently no claim can be made in relation to the trial against him; he will not be asked for any compensation for the damage and no punishment.
After the hearing of the founder of the legal power of the gambling house, at 15:50 hours the immediate freedom of Larrazabal Bret<0xC3><0xB3>n was ordered.
The Registrar of the Tribunal, Jorge Y<0xC3><0xA1>nez, moved to the prison of the municipality of San Nicol<0xC3><0xA1>s de los Garza to inform Jon<0xC3><0xA1>s that he had been pardoned legally and his file would be classified.
