Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali typewriter has gone down in history as the man who confirmed the death of Alfonso Cano.
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4, a CTI fingerprintist from Cali went down in history as the person who confirmed the identity of the supreme leader of the FARC: "Alfonso Cano", by confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven typewriters working in local ITC offices, this week it was the turn of Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, a Puerto Tejada man who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
Early in his career, Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez worked in Choc<0xC3><0xB3> municipalities, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to where the bodies were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he moved to the capital of Valle and after taking appropriate courses, he specialized in fingerprintoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to take the map with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo Le<0xC3><0xB3>n S<0xC3><0xA1>enz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the place of the body, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as this one was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much leaner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a pickup and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those on the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinz<0xC3><0xB3>n that yes, he was the supreme leader of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typewriter from Sij<0xC3><0xAD>n de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
In addition to identifying the bodies, fingerprintoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When caught, many offenders present false ID cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove a part of the wall of a house, because in this place the thief had pressed his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different thefts,” he recalls.
Footprints can also screen or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently, a dead man was found, with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a relative may be suspected of the crime and indeed a print on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee that he's the killer, it puts him on the scene of the crime.
An ITC fingerprintist explained that "the fingerprints of objects are extracted with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a stripper or strip is used to remove them.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the declensioners’ database, or to the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still a lot of Colombians without papers,” the ITC expert said.
He explained that not everything is as shown in the CSI television program.
As all that glitters is not gold, all that one touches does not necessarily become an imprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
